rdisziplinären Forschungsgespräch im weiten Horizont der christlichen Transformierung der spätantiken Lebenswelt und Kultur einen besonderen Stellenwert beanspruchen.  aThe first modern, text-critical edition of the Epistula ad Marcellinum by Athanasius of Alexandria presents all of the transmitted manuscripts including the Oriental versions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn Greek, Ancient (to 1453).0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 4aAltertumswisssenschaften. 4aAthanasius. 4aTextedition. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / History.2bisacsh  aAthansius.  aClassical Studies.  atext edition.1 aSavvidis, Kyriakos, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWyrwa, Dietmar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021z9783110753974oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311070317740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311070516440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110705164423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110705164.jpg  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2021